Half Pi Plugin Exception to AGPL-3.0
======================================

Copyright (c) 2026 Sheyiyuan

This file clarifies the licensing of plugins, extensions, and modules that
interoperate with Half Pi but are not part of the Half Pi core repository.

1. Definitions

   "Plugins" means any software module, skill package, tool, or extension
   that communicates with Half Pi through its documented interfaces
   (including but not limited to: tool registration, skill loading, the
   Face protocol, the Hand protocol, or event hooks) and is distributed
   separately from the Half Pi core repository.

2. Exception

   Notwithstanding the terms of Section 5 and Section 13 of the
   GNU Affero General Public License version 3 (AGPL-3.0), Plugins as
   defined above are NOT considered derivative works of Half Pi and are
   NOT required to be licensed under AGPL-3.0 or any GPL-compatible
   license.

   Plugin authors may license their work under any terms of their choosing.

3. Intent

   The purpose of this exception is to foster a healthy plugin ecosystem
   around Half Pi — allowing community members to write and share tools,
   skills, and extensions without legal uncertainty or forced copyleft
   contamination.

   The Half Pi core itself (the contents of this repository) remains
   under the full terms of AGPL-3.0, ensuring that the project is and
   always will be free software.
